Phase 2 Implementation Plan — Labourious
Date: 2026-06-17

Estimated Duration: 4 weeks (5 days/week, 8h/day)

Total Tasks: 25 (TDD order)

Deliverables: Complete agent engine, WebSocket server, MVP warroom, backtesting CLI

Success Metric: 5+ concurrent agents trading live via Alpaca/Binance; warroom dashboard live P&L updates <200ms

Architecture Overview
Execution Flow:
APScheduler (60s intervals per agent)
  ↓
Agent Orchestrator loads agent config + context file
  ↓
Fetch Market Data (cache: symbol → {price, RSI, MA20, ...})
  ↓
LLM Router (Ollama or Claude) → TradeDecision
  ↓
Risk Manager checks confidence/losses/drawdown
  ↓
Approval Gate (autonomous / human-in-loop / risk-based)
  ↓
Trade Executor: position sizing → paper simulation OR live broker order
  ↓
WebSocket broadcast: agent_update, trade_executed, portfolio_update
  ↓
Frontend store dispatch → warroom re-render
Layer isolation: Each module (llm, brokers, trading, orchestrator) is independent and async-first. Shared state: market data cache dict + connection manager. No mutable agent state outside DB.

